CUPID'S DART was hustled along in range around the three path, under right handed urging from the five path at the top of the stretch, and flattened. I FOUND IT set the pace in the two path, was roused early around the turn, headed by an outer foe nearing the quarter pole, yielded passing the eighth pole, and brushed with an outer foe late. PACIFIC LEGEND tracked along the inside but was empty from around the two path in the stretch. WHISKEYONHISLIPS chased in the two path but was no menace.
